      "options": {
        "mode": "markdown",
        "code": {
          "language": "plaintext",
          "showLineNumbers": false,
          "showMiniMap": false
        },
        "content": "## Ninety-nine cabinets, three sovereign networks, one operations view.\n\nGDOT, NCDOT, and SCDOT each run ~33 cabinets \u2014 99 in all \u2014 reporting device heartbeats, controller mode, and faults. The map shows the whole network at a glance, the pie shows the Econolite / McCain vendor split, and the fault table plus per-cabinet drill-downs take an operator from \"which state DOT has a problem\" to \"which controller\" without leaving the page."
      }
    },
    {
      "datasource": {
        "type": "grafana-clickhouse-datasource",
        "uid": "clickhouse-vikasa"
      },
      "description": "One cluster marker per state (GA/NC/SC), aggregated from all 99 cabinets in vikasa_federation.cabinets (not scoped to the $dot selector). Marker is positioned at the state's cabinet centroid, labeled with its cabinet count, and colored by that state's worst (max) heartbeat freshness. Freshness is computed from the UNION of the 3 per-DOT heartbeats tables (vikasa_gdot/ncdot/scdot) since vikasa_federation.heartbeats only carries the 3 corridor cabinets' events (DMZ shares corridor data only) \u2014 the union covers all 99 cabinets' real freshness.",
      "fieldConfig": {
        "defaults": {
          "color": {
            "mode": "thresholds"
          },
          "custom": {
            "hideFrom": {
              "legend": false,
              "tooltip": false,
              "viz": false
            }
          },
          "mappings": [],
          "unit": "s",
          "thresholds": {
            "mode": "absolute",
            "steps": [
              {
                "color": "green",
                "value": null
              },
              {
                "color": "yellow",
                "value": 30
              },
              {
                "color": "red",
